\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
• For anaemic spleens (AS) it is best to refilter the cell suspension through
 a 70µm sieve, as this removes larger debris.
 Several washes with PBS and refiltering through 40um sieve will help to
 eliminate crud and get a good single cell suspension, giving cells that
